 the twenty-first century? Are they capable of playing their roles in ways that will foster rather than betray the public interest? These are among the questions explored in When Parties Prosper, a richly comparative, up-to-date, and accessible study of political parties in power in Europe, Asia, and the Americas. Each country study in the book reviews the country's political history, describes its present party system, provides a detailed study of the one or two most powerful parties in the system, and evaluates the impact the parties have on government efficacy, stability, and democratic legitimacy. Two broadly comparative chapters highlight differences and similarities across the countries. Following a common structure, the authors offer answers to their core questions—but they are answers that are sure to stimulate discussion, disagreement, and reassessment.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / Political Parties.2bisacsh1 aBösch, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFukui, Haruhiro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaegel, Florence, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJoignant, Alfredo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKolodny, Robin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrupavičius, Algis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKubiak, Hieronim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKulik, Anatoly, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLanzaro, Jorge, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLawson, Kay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLawson, Kay, eeditor.4e